news.title: Skanska says rising interest rates, costs dim outlook in Europe
news.para: Third-quarter order bookings in Skanska's construction arm rose by 50% from a year earlier and by 17.4% versus the second quarter to 43.8 billion Swedish crowns adjusted for currency effects.

news.title: Canada's Ontario ups foreign home buyers speculation tax to 25%
news.para: Ontario, home to Canada's financial capital of Toronto, is projected to have more new households than new homes by 2030, according to Canada's national housing agency.

news.title: Housing sales to exceed 3.6 lakh units in seven cities in 2022: Anarock
news.para: The January-September period of 2022 saw housing sales and new launches surpass the full-year readings of 2019 with approx. 2.73 lakh units sold in 9M 2022 and new launches at 2.65 lakh units.

news.title: Goa-based Sun Estates in talks to raise $50 million
news.para: “Foreign funds are not hesitant anymore to invest in holiday destinations and even the developers of metro cities want to come to this part of the country. We are getting a lot of offer for joint development and at the same time we are looking to raise funds to fast track the development,” said Suraj Morajkar, managing director, Sun Estates.

news.title: Nashik civic body chief wants cluster development of gaothans
news.para: The state government had introduced the unified development control promotion and regulations (UDCPR) in December 2020. The new unified DCPR includes development for gaothan areas, but the area requirement is at least 4,000 sqmt (1 acre) of land.

news.title: LSGD issues draft notification for master plan of Kovalam-Vizhinjam
news.para: The notification says that zoning regulations are not intended to prohibit existing uses that have been lawfully established prior to the enforcement of the new regulations.

news.title: MahaMetro gets tag of planning authority to develop prime lands
news.para: The state government has now given "special planning authority status" to MahaMetro to look after these lands "in larger public interest".

news.title: Mumbai: Three of six Dharavi redevelopment bids will qualify, says minister
news.para: Last week, the Union railway ministry had signed a definitive agreement with the Dharavi Redevelopment Authority to hand over 47.5 acres of railway land in Dadar for the redevelopment project.

news.title: Emaar fraud accused seeks discharge from CBI case, cites failure of agency
news.para: The Emaar case involves alleged misuse of land and its sale proceeds in violation of the agreement between Emaar and the then Andhra Pradesh Industrial Infrastructure Corporation (APIIC), cheating the state of a few thousand crores in revenue.

news.title: Noida Authority probes plot auctions quoting up to 110 times base price
news.para: The Noida Authority had put up 241 plots for auction and received 184 applications against them. Of these 184, there were 14 applications where the exorbitant rates had been quoted.

news.title: Haryana RERA orders Ramprastha developers to refund buyer with interest
news.para: The complainant, who booked a unit in Skyz project in Sector 37C in July 2011, approached the authority in December 2019 wishing to withdraw from the project and demanding refund as the builder failed to give possession on due date which was July 2014. The developer did not respond to queries sent by TOI.

news.title: Egypt's SODIC offers to buy Orascom Real Estate for $125 million
news.para: Abu Dhabi's Aldar Properties and state holding company ADQ bought a controlling stake in SODIC late last year, and the purchase of Orascom Real Estate would further expand their Egyptian real estate business.

news.title: China's revenue from government land sales falls 26.4% in September 2022
news.para: Government revenue from land sales fell 26.4% year-on-year in September after a 4.9% drop in August, according to Reuters calculations based on official data, weighed on by still-stretched financing conditions for developers and weak property market sentiment.

news.title: Delhi LG launches one-time property tax amnesty scheme 'SAMRIDDHI 2022-23'
news.para: Under the scheme, residential property owners can pay just the principal property tax amount of the current and of the past five years.

news.title: Home First Finance Company's net profit rises 21% in Q2 FY23
news.para: The board of directors of the company approved to offer, issue and allot in one or more tranches, non-convertible debentures (NCDs) or such other structured instruments for an amount not exceeding Rs 500 crore by way of private placement.
